item.description:
Webhooks are a way to enable bi-directional communication via the API.

The concept is simple - you subscribe to one of our existing events (which can be fetched using the `List available events` endpoint) and provide a target URL.

This URL needs to be a valid, publicly reachable, HTTPS URL

If an event of the given type, for example `timeEntryCreated` is triggered, the URL you provided will be called with a `POST` request, containing the event payload as JSON.

Examples for the currently available events and their payloads can be found below.

This enables you to build systems, which react on changes made in your EARLY data. For example, you could write a tool which turns your light switch on and off if you start, or stop a Tracking. Or you know, something actually useful... ;)

The possibilities are endless here and this API also finally makes it possible to integrate with tools such as [Zapier](https://zapier.com/apps/early/integrations)!

## Available Events:

### Time Entries

- timeEntryCreated

- timeEntryUpdated

- timeEntryDeleted


### Tracking

- trackingStarted

- trackingStopped

- trackingEdited

- trackingCanceled


### Activities

- activityCreated

- activityUpdated

- activityDeleted


### Folders

- folderCreated

- folderUpdated

- folderDeleted


### Leaves

- timeLeaveCreated

- timeLeaveUpdated

- timeLeaveDeleted

- timeLeaveApproved

- timeLeaveDenied


